Author: darkzet
Content:
this is probably a midnight overthinking thoughts LOL

warning : (thing might be some kind of vent but dw its actually not that deep) 

im on school holidays for 40 days! 
this happens because im transitioning to tahun ajaran baru, and before that, theres a MONTH long of holiday break. 

i am an ACTIVE student in my school, i know almost half of the students in my school, i joined organizations, extracurricular and all that extra activities, now when its all gone, i kinda feel empty rn. 

at this moment of no pressure, no demands and no direction, idk how to feel better about my self, i have a lot of friends at school, but that happens because we have a shared schedule. theres barely anyone who talks to me outside of school. 

can anyone suggest what i should do in this long holiday of mine rn?

Author: edennottheproject
Content: Is this your first university summer vacation?

Author: edennottheproject
Content: If yes then it is TOTALLY NORMAL to feel this way! You went from loads of exciting social engagements etc and then baam! Nothing

Author: edennottheproject
Content: I would set a target for myself - is there one thing i want to improve about myself? If yes, how should I do it? And make that your defining part of your holiday

Author: edennottheproject
Content: Ngegym? Travel? Belajar masak? Creative project? Choose one and lock in

Author: chewiezzz
Content: it's time to get to know yourself more by exploring different activities you have interest in, just like what eden has said above
